        "header": "Abstract",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.14366/2603.14366v1/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:REPA degrades JiT performance.As training progresses, JiT++REPA yields higher FID[heusel2017gans](↓\\downarrow) than vanilla JiT, indicating that REPA hinders pixel space diffusion training.\nPixelREPA prevents overfitting to the external semantic feature target, which accelerates convergence in JiT training.\nRemarkably, PixelREPA achieves>2×>2\\timesfaster convergence than the vanilla JiT.\nAll evaluated models utilize JiT-B/16/16.",
                "position": 258
            }
        ]
